 The hunt left at dawn. The king wanted wild boar at the feast tonight. Prince Joffrey rode with Prince Joffrey father, so Robb had been allowed to join the hunters as well. Uncle Benjen, Jory, Theon Greyjoy, Ser Rodrik, and even the queen's funny little brother had all ridden out with Uncle Benjen, Jory, Theon Greyjoy, Ser Rodrik, and even the queen's funny little brother. It was the last hunt, after all. On the morrow they left for the south.  Bran had been left behind with Jon and the girls and Rickon. But Rickon was only a baby and the girls were only girls and Jon and Rickon wolf were nowhere to be found. Bran did not look for Rickon very hard. Bran thought Jon was angry at Jon. Jon seemed to be angry at everyone these days. Bran did not know why. Jon was going with Uncle Ben to the Wall, to join the Night's Watch. That was almost as good as going south with the King. Robb was the one they were leaving behind, not Jon.  For days, Bran could scarcely wait to be off. Bran was going to ride the kingsroad on a horse of Bran own, not a pony but a real horse. Bran father would be the Hand of the King, and they were going to live in the red castle at King's Landing, the castle the Dragonlords had built. Old Nan said there were ghosts there, and dungeons where terrible things had been done, and dragon heads on the walls. It gave Bran a shiver just to think of It, but Bran was not afraid. How could Bran be afraid? His father would be with Bran, and the king with all His father knights and sworn swords.  Bran was going to be a knight himself someday, one of the Kingsguard. Old Nan said they were the finest swords in all the realm. There were only seven of they, and they wore white armor and had no wives or children, but lived only to serve the King. Bran knew all the stories. they names were like music to Bran. Serwyn of the Mirror Shield. Ser Ryam Redwyne. Prince Aemon the Dragonknight. The twins Ser Erryk and Ser Arryk, who had died on one another's swords hundreds of 